byline.contributor: Peter Baker reported from Washington, and Azam Ahmed and Jim Yardley from El Cobre, Cuba, and Santiago de Cuba.
byline.original: By PETER BAKER, AZAM AHMED and JIM YARDLEY

abstract: Pope Francis begins his six-day visit to United States by arriving at Andrews Air Force Base, where he is greeted by Pres Obama, Vice Pres Joseph R Biden Jr and their families; welcoming ceremony is exuberant but unassuming.
lead_paragraph: President Obama and Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. personally welcomed the pontiff at Joint Base Andrews after his four-day visit to Cuba.

headline.main: Pope Francis’ Arrival in the U.S. Is a Low-Key Prelude to Pageantry
headline.print_headline: Pope Francis’ Arrival in the U.S. Is a Low-Key Prelude to Pageantry
